args: This Saint Starfall costume is\nsimply sensational!

Agreed! Looks like our group effort to
design a costume paid off. It's not a
proper holiday unless your outfit shows
some spirit!
It made me think I might have a future\nin costume-making! Aha ha.
I must say, Malora—we couldn't have\nasked for a better model. Your proportions\nreally bring out the best in the costume.
Oho ho! Aren't you just the sweetest thing?
Y'know, since you're dressed as Saint\nStarfall and all... Why not go whole\nholiday hog and act the part, too?
A fascinating proposition—and trust me, I\nknow my propositions! Now, what would\nSaint Starfall do? ...Aha! Gift-giving!

Perhaps I'll try giving out some special
gifts—a letter sealed with a kiss, or a
spare key to my bedroom, or some
more...worldly pleasures.
Wh-which gutter did you unceremoniously\nscoop THAT idea out of?!
Aw, you're no fun. Well, perhaps I can\nrustle up something a tad more...\nfamily-friendly.
As in, maybe I'll quietly slip into the home\nof a nice, happy family, and leave gifts for\nthem. And then...
And then, in exchange for the gifts, I'll\ntake the handsome man of the house back\nwith me and make him one of my reindeer!
Come on, can't you just give out presents\nlike a normal person?
But that's so blasé without anything to\nspice it up! Gift-giving should excite the\nsenses and thrill the heart!
I'm not sure your idea of a ＂thrill＂ is\nreally in line with the spirit of the season.
Hmm. I wonder what I can do to give my\ninterpretation of Saint Starfall a little of\nthat oh-so-juicy Malora zest...
Excuse me! Is this the Halidom?!
Oh, a visitor! Do you need something?
I need you to look for someone!\nWe haven't been in contact for several\ndays, and...and... *sob*
Something tells me there's more to this\nstory. Let's hear it, miss.
So the person you seek is a lover who\ndisappeared.
Yes. He just vanished one day without\na word. I'm so worried about him...
I-it'll be okay. Vanessa and the others are\noff gathering information right now.
And they'll definitely find him, right?\nAnd then he'll come back to me...
Tell me: Was this beau of yours\nstruggling to make ends meet?
Well, yes, actually. He made a mistake at\nwork—one that he said would cost a\ngreat deal of money to compensate for...
And what did you do when he told you?

I gave him all the money I had, of course.
And a necklace I was quite attached to.
He promised he would return them to me
afterwards...
Do I have to spell it out for you?\nListen up. This so-called ＂lover＂ of yours...
We're back. And wo-MAN, am I furious.
You'll probably feel the same in a sec.\nWe heard something absolutely outrageous\nwhen we went out to gather info.
It would seem that the only thing our\nmissing lover swoons over is cold, hard\ncash.
A con artist, yes. He gets close to his\ntargets, feeds them some trumped-up line\nabout being pressed for cash, and bam.
He shakes poor ladies down for every gold\npiece they're worth, then ghosts 'em. He's\nhad more than his share of victims, too.
I had just arrived from Peng Lai, and he\nwas so kind to me in my hour of need...\nNow I see that was all just an act.
I loved him with all my heart, and he\nplayed me for everything save the\nclothes off my back. What a fool I am.
Hey, that two-faced creep is the one who's\nat fault here, not you. Don't cry, okay?
And yet I can't stop thinking about him.\nIt's mortifying. Wretched.
You silly girl. Love is a battle,\nand she who falls first loses the war.
Hey, take it easy on the poor gal.
However, showing due respect to the\ncritically lovestruck is the victor's duty.

He who opens the door to the realm of
passion is beholden to his charge until
the bittersweet end. Love is the legacy
he is honor-bound to leave behind.
Tell me: Would you leave this matter in\nmy hands? I'll catch that miscreant for\nyou—this I swear!
But we have no idea where he is.\nHe's hidden himself quite well.
That won't be a problem.\nJust leave it to me.
Y-you certainly seem confident.\nWhat makes you so sure?

My mother was a bounty hunter, so I've
inherited certain...weapons from her.
I'll use them to nab our swindler before
you can say the word ＂heartbreak.＂
Then, um... I'd really appreciate your help,\nSaint Starfall.
Done and done. But hmm...Saint Starfall?\nI daresay I'm too sexy to be a saint.
Meaning that I will not be known as\nSaint Starfall, but as LADY STARFALL!\nAnd with that, I'm off! Ta-ta!
Yes! I may not be a particularly saintly\nwoman, but I AM rather fastidious\nwhen it comes to matters of love.

This holiday, your gift shall be the
satisfaction of a stolen treasure returned,
courtesy of the great and bewitching
Lady Starfall!
